Dr '''Issam Nassar''' ({{lang-ar|<big>عصام نصار</big>}}), is a [[Palestinian people|Palestinian]] historian of [[History of photography|photography]] in Palestine and the [[Middle East]].<ref>[http://history.illinoisstate.edu/people/?control=facultyProfile&ID=irnassa&dept=History Issam Nassar] Faculty Bio</ref> He is professor of History at [[Illinois State University]] and a research fellow at the [[Institute for Palestine Studies]]. He taught at the [[University of California]] at [[University of California, Berkeley|Berkeley]] in 2006; Bradley University in 2003–2006 and al-Quds University in 1998–2003.
Nassar is the co-editor of ''[[Hawliyat al-Quds|Jerusalem Quarterly]]'' ({{lang-ar|Hawliyat al-Quds}}) and author of a number of books and articles, among them ''Laqatat Mughayirah'' (''Different Snapshots: The History of Early Local Photography in Palestine'').
